title: Pakistan: Blast in Lahore leaves at least one dead, says rescue official
text:
Pakistan: Blast in Lahore leaves at least one dead, says rescue official Pakistan: Blast in Lahore leaves at least one dead, says rescue official Initial reports on Pakistani television channel Geo News said a generator had exploded but reports at the scene speculated that a bomb had gone off, based on the extent of the damage. By: Reuters | Lahore | Published:February 23, 2017 1:14 pm Pakistan has been struck by a wave of terrorist attacks in recent weeks, killing at least 130 people across the country and leaving hundreds wounded. 
A blast at a market in Pakistan’s eastern city of Lahore killed at least one person on Thursday and wounded eight, a rescue official told Reuters. The cause of the explosion was not immediately clear. 
Watch What Else is Making News 
Initial reports on Pakistani television channel Geo News said a generator had exploded but reports at the scene speculated that a bomb had gone off, based on the extent of the damage.
